      </section>

      <!-- Steps to Get Started -->
      <section id="steps">
        <h2>7 Steps to Get Started</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Create an Account:</strong> Sign up for a LexisNexis account and verify your email.</li>
          <li><strong>Set Up Your Profile:</strong> Complete your user profile and set notification preferences.</li>
          <li><strong>Download & Install:</strong> Install any necessary desktop applications or browser extensions.</li>
          <li><strong>Connect Data Sources:</strong> Link public and private databases to your workspace.</li>
          <li><strong>Configure Permissions:</strong> Assign roles and access levels to team members.</li>
          <li><strong>Explore Key Features:</strong> Try basic and advanced search, legal analytics, and report generation.</li>
          <li><strong>Customize Your Dashboard:</strong> Tailor your dashboard to display the metrics and documents most relevant to you.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Projects Section -->
      <section id="projects">
        <h2>Projects</h2>
        <p>Projects in LexisNexis allow you to organize research around a specific case, deal, or analysis. Learn how to create, manage, and collaborate on projects.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Boards Section -->
      <section id="boards">
        <h2>Boards</h2>
        <p>Boards provide a visual way to track tasks, research progress, and case statuses. Discover how to create boards, add cards, and customize workflows.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Issues & Filters Section -->
      <section id="issues">
        <h2>Issues & Filters</h2>
        <p>Use Issues and Filters to track tasks, assign action items, and create custom queries. This section covers creating issues, using filters, and saving searches.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Reports & Insights Section -->
      <section id="reports">
        <h2>Reports & Insights</h2>
        <p>Generate detailed reports and gain insights with our analytics tools. Learn how to customize reports, schedule automated runs, and interpret results.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Apps & Integrations Section -->
